Connecticut
-----------
<http://dep.state.ct.us/mosquito/index.asp> [edited
21 Aug 2000
The State announced 11 additional WNV positive crows including one from
Bridgeport (a new town). Birds were collected from Bridgeport (1), Darien (2),
Fairfield (3), Stamford (3), West Hartford (2). No spraying is recommended
at this time. To date, 61 birds have tested positive for WNV -- 60 crows and
one robin -- in 16 different communities.
New York State
--------------
<http://www.health.state.ny.us/nysdoh/westnile/update/today.htm> [edited
Today, the New York State Health Department's Wadsworth Laboratory reported
39 West Nile Virus positive dead birds from the following counties: Albany,
1; Broome, 1; Nassau, 7; New York City, 7 (Staten Island 2, Manhattan 2,
Brooklyn 1, Bronx 2); Orange, 1; Rockland, 11; Saratoga, 1; Schenectady, 1;
Suffolk, 4; Ulster, 2 and Westchester, 3. Eight positive mosquito pools also
were reported: New York City, 8 (Staten Island 4, Manhattan 3, Queens 1).
One West Nile Virus positive live wild bird was reported in Bronx county.
The total number of West Nile Virus positive specimens for New York State
this year is 279 birds, 140 mosquito pools, 1 sentinel chicken, 6 live wild
birds and 3 human cases.
See also: Map - WNV Positive Humans, Birds, and Mosquitoes - August 21, 2000
[JPG image - 533 KB The map is also available as a Portable Document
Format (PDF) file - 348 KB. Note: Set your printer for landscape printing if
you encounter difficulty printing this map.
Westchester County, New York, Dept. of Health
--------------------------------------------
[edited
21 Aug 2000
The Westchester County Department of Health was notified by the New York
State Department of Health today that three more birds have tested positive
for West Nile virus. The three new positive birds are all crows. Two crows
were collected from Sleepy Hollow and one crow was collected from Mount
Pleasant. Communities are to be sprayed as a result of these new birds
identified with West Nile virus and the dates for spraying will be
announced tomorrow.
[These are the same 3 birds reported positive for Westchester Co. in the
NYS update above. - Mod.JW
